[For maps of Uzbekistan, go to http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/uzbekistan.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2757479,41356. Surkhandaryinsky or Surxondaryo or Surkhondaryo is the southernmost oblast of Uzbekistan. For Uzun, go to http://www.maplandia.com/uzbekistan/surkhandarya/uzun/.

I greatly appreciate Sabine's and Natalia's work with this report and translation. The original report was written by an Uzbek person who does not have Russian as the primary native language. This probably explains the various anomalies in the script as to numbers and dates, but the overall story is clear enough, and one we hear frequently in Central Asia -- of sick cattle (with anthrax) being slaughtered and butchered, followed by human cases with cutaneous lesions. Whether gastroenteric cases followed upon the eating and marketing (outside the slaughtering and butchering group) of this meat has yet to be revealed. It also reinforces the impression that livestock anthrax is still out of control in eastern and southern Uzbekistan in spite of the claims of vaccinating 14 million head of livestock earlier this year (2014). - Mod.MHJ]
